# Project Roadmap

This document outlines the development plan for the English Vocabulary App across a 3-month period.

## Month 1: Backend Core and Foundation

### Week 1-2: Setup and Authentication
- Project structure setup
- Domain entities implementation
- User authentication with JWT
- Basic API endpoints

### Week 3-4: Core Features
- Word and WordSet management
- User progress tracking
- Spaced repetition algorithm basics
- Initial database seeding

## Month 2: Frontend Development and Integration

### Week 5-6: Frontend Foundation
- React project setup
- UI component development
- Authentication UI
- API integration

### Week 7-8: Core Feature Implementation
- Flashcard system
- Word management interface
- Study session tracking
- Progress visualization

## Month 3: Advanced Features and Refinement

### Week 9-10: Advanced Learning Features
- Mobile responsiveness
- Offline capabilities
- Advanced study algorithms
- Content enrichment

### Week 11-12: Testing and Deployment
- Unit and integration testing
- Performance optimization
- Documentation
- Deployment preparation

## Feature Priority

### Must-have (MVP)
- User authentication
- Basic word management
- Simple flashcard study system
- Basic progress tracking

### Should-have
- Spaced repetition algorithm
- Word sets and categorization
- Study statistics and reports
- Mobile-responsive design

### Could-have
- Offline functionality
- Social features (sharing word sets)
- Gamification elements
- Multiple learning modes

## Implementation Strategy

1. Start with a minimal viable product (MVP) focusing on core features
2. Use an iterative approach, adding features incrementally
3. Prioritize features based on learning effectiveness
4. Regularly test with users to gather feedback

## Next Development Focus

- Complete domain model implementation
- Set up database context and repositories
- Implement authentication endpoints
- Create basic word management API
